<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="175" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1623,395,876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="175">
It must remain doubtful whether these two records (and that of 
<emphasis box="[1481,1617,662,703]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="175">cretense</emphasis>
above) are really referable to 
<emphasis box="[734,960,705,746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="175">xanthostma,</emphasis>
since a series of subspecies or races are known from Asia Minor, Caucasia, Syria, etc., and in Cyprus a t least there 
<emphasis box="[192,223,794,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="175">is</emphasis>
a form very close to 
<emphasis box="[645,858,793,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="175">xanthostma</emphasis>
but which has both heteromorphic and homoeomorphic females.
</paragraph>
